Detailed Description

Point holds two integer coordinates. 

 //create Point object and initialize with assigned coordinates.
 Point *pt1 = new Point(5,5);
 //create Point object and assigned coordinates by set() function.
 Point *pt2 = new Point();
 pt2->set(3,3);
 //test if point is equal to assigned coordinates.
 pt1->equals(3,3);
 //negate coordinates
 pt2->negate();   //pt2 now is (-3,-3)
